# Putonghua Learning Game - Minimal Design Prototype

## 1. Visual Design Philosophy
- **Minimalist Approach**:
  - Simple, clean interface
  - Focus on text and interaction
  - Minimal graphical elements
- **Image Generation Strategy**:
  - Use AI-generated images sparingly
  - Focus on key narrative moments
  - Avoid complex visual requirements

## 2. Narrative Generation

### 2.1 Dynamic Story Creation
- **LLM-Driven Narrative**:
  - Use AWS Bedrock for content generation
  - Create flexible story templates
  - Generate unique storylines each playthrough
- **Narrative Parameters**:
  - HSK level-specific vocabulary
  - Cultural learning contexts
  - Interactive decision points

### 2.2 Story Structure
- **Core Components**:
  - 3-5 narrative templates
  - 2-3 decision points per story
  - Clear learning objectives
- **Generation Constraints**:
  - Maintain language learning focus
  - Ensure grammatical accuracy
  - Align with selected HSK level

## 3. Technical Implementation

### 3.1 Technology Stack
- **Game Engine**: Ren'Py
- **Backend**: Flask microservice
- **LLM Integration**: AWS Bedrock
- **Text-to-Speech**: gTTS or Azure Cognitive Services

### 3.2 Language Learning Features
- **HSK Level Support**:
  - Levels 1-4 initially
  - Adaptive content difficulty
- **Text Display**:
  - Hanzi and Pinyin toggle
  - Inline language explanations
- **Audio Features**:
  - Text-to-speech generation
  - Pronunciation guidance

## 4. Minimal Visual Design

### 4.1 Interface Considerations
- **Color Scheme**:
  - Neutral, clean palette
  - High contrast for readability
- **Layout**:
  - Text-centered design
  - Simple navigation
  - Minimal graphical distractions

### 4.2 Image Integration
- **AI Image Generation**:
  - 1-2 images per story
  - Focus on key narrative moments
  - Simple, evocative illustrations
- **Image Selection Criteria**:
  - Relevance to story context
  - Cultural appropriateness
  - Minimal complexity

## 5. Development Roadmap

### 5.1 Weekly Milestones
- **Week 1**:
  - Narrative template design
  - LLM integration prototype
  - Basic UI framework
- **Week 2**:
  - Story generation testing
  - Language feature implementation
  - User experience refinement

## 6. Prototype Goals
- Demonstrate dynamic story generation
- Provide engaging language learning experience
- Validate LLM-driven narrative approach

## 7. Technical Considerations
- Manage API call complexity
- Ensure consistent narrative quality
- Maintain language learning effectiveness